            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWhat%20a%20sight%20it%20must%20have%20been%20when%20the%20song%20of%20the%20Lord%20was%20again%20sung%20in%20Jerusalem%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20almost%20a%20century!%20Seventy%20years%20of%20captivity%20in%20cruel%20Babylon%20gave%20way%20to%20a%20restoration%20of%20praise%20and%20worship.%20With%20praise%2C%20thanksgiving%2C%20and%20shouting%2C%20the%20people%20of%20God%20jubilantly%20rejoiced%2C%20saying%2C%20%22He%20is%20so%20good!%20His%20faithful%20love%20for%20Israel%20endures%20forever!%22%20(Ezra%203%3A11).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EEven%20today%20God%20is%20restoring%20praise%20and%20worship%20to%20His%20Church.%20Ezra%203%3A13%20tells%20us%20that%20%22the%20joyful%20shouting%20and%20weeping%20mingled%20together%20in%20a%20loud%20commotion%20that%20could%20be%20heard%20far%20in%20the%20distance.%22%20And%20so%20will%20our%20praise%20be%20heard%20by%20a%20lost%20world%20that%20is%20waiting%20for%20some%20sound%20of%20the%20joy%20of%20the%20Lord.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20hates%20the%20praises%20of%20God%2C%20for%20they%20represent%20a%20regathered%20people%2C%20a%20determined%20people%2C%20and%20an%20evangelistic%20people.%20Also%2C%20some%20people%20will%20not%20understand%20our%20praise%20because%20the%20man%20without%20the%20Spirit%20does%20not%20understand%20those%20things%20that%20come%20from%20the%20Spirit%20of%20God%20(1%20Corinthians%202%3A14).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPraise%20releases%20the%20waiting%20hand%20of%20God.%20Decide%20today%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20%22praising%20crowd.%22%20After%20all%2C%20that%20is%20your%20destiny%20throughout%20all%20eternity!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
