            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Ezra.3:1-4:23",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EEzra%203%3A1-4%3A23%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_1%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EEzra%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Altar%20Is%20Rebuilt%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20early%20autumn%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20seventh%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20year%20is%20not%20specified%2C%20so%20it%20may%20have%20been%20during%20Cyrus%26%23x2019%3Bs%20first%20year%20(538%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E)%20or%20second%20year%20(537%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E).%20The%20seventh%20month%20of%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20occurred%20within%20the%20months%20of%20September%2FOctober%20538%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20October%2FNovember%20537%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20when%20the%20Israelites%20had%20settled%20in%20their%20towns%2C%20all%20the%20people%20assembled%20in%20Jerusalem%20with%20a%20unified%20purpose.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_2%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Jeshua%20son%20of%20Jehozadak%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A2%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EJozadak%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20a%20variant%20spelling%20of%20Jehozadak%3B%20also%20in%203%3A8.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20joined%20his%20fellow%20priests%20and%20Zerubbabel%20son%20of%20Shealtiel%20with%20his%20family%20in%20rebuilding%20the%20altar%20of%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%20They%20wanted%20to%20sacrifice%20burnt%20offerings%20on%20it%2C%20as%20instructed%20in%20the%20Law%20of%20Moses%2C%20the%20man%20of%20God.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_3%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EEven%20though%20the%20people%20were%20afraid%20of%20the%20local%20residents%2C%20they%20rebuilt%20the%20altar%20at%20its%20old%20site.%20Then%20they%20began%20to%20sacrifice%20burnt%20offerings%20on%20the%20altar%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20each%20morning%20and%20evening.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_4%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20celebrated%20the%20Festival%20of%20Shelters%20as%20prescribed%20in%20the%20Law%2C%20sacrificing%20the%20number%20of%20burnt%20offerings%20specified%20for%20each%20day%20of%20the%20festival.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_5%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20also%20offered%20the%20regular%20burnt%20offerings%20and%20the%20offerings%20required%20for%20the%20new%20moon%20celebrations%20and%20the%20annual%20festivals%20as%20prescribed%20by%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20The%20people%20also%20gave%20voluntary%20offerings%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_6%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EFifteen%20days%20before%20the%20Festival%20of%20Shelters%20began%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3EOn%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20seventh%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20day%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20occurred%20in%20September%20or%20October.%20The%20Festival%20of%20Shelters%20began%20on%20the%20fifteenth%20day%20of%20the%20seventh%20month.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20the%20priests%20had%20begun%20to%20sacrifice%20burnt%20offerings%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20This%20was%20even%20before%20they%20had%20started%20to%20lay%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_7%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20People%20Begin%20to%20Rebuild%20the%20Temple%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20people%20hired%20masons%20and%20carpenters%20and%20bought%20cedar%20logs%20from%20the%20people%20of%20Tyre%20and%20Sidon%2C%20paying%20them%20with%20food%2C%20wine%2C%20and%20olive%20oil.%20The%20logs%20were%20brought%20down%20from%20the%20Lebanon%20mountains%20and%20floated%20along%20the%20coast%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A7%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20sea.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20Joppa%2C%20for%20King%20Cyrus%20had%20given%20permission%20for%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_8%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20construction%20of%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20began%20in%20midspring%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20second%20month.%3C%2Fem%3E%20This%20month%20in%20the%20ancient%20Hebrew%20lunar%20calendar%20occurred%20within%20the%20months%20of%20April%20and%20May%20536%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-sc%22%3Eb.c.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20during%20the%20second%20year%20after%20they%20arrived%20in%20Jerusalem.%20The%20work%20force%20was%20made%20up%20of%20everyone%20who%20had%20returned%20from%20exile%2C%20including%20Zerubbabel%20son%20of%20Shealtiel%2C%20Jeshua%20son%20of%20Jehozadak%20and%20his%20fellow%20priests%2C%20and%20all%20the%20Levites.%20The%20Levites%20who%20were%20twenty%20years%20old%20or%20older%20were%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20rebuilding%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_9%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20workers%20at%20the%20Temple%20of%20God%20were%20supervised%20by%20Jeshua%20with%20his%20sons%20and%20relatives%2C%20and%20Kadmiel%20and%20his%20sons%2C%20all%20descendants%20of%20Hodaviah.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E3%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Esons%20of%20Judah%3C%2Fem%3E%20(i.e.%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebene%20Yehudah%3C%2Fem%3E).%20%3Cem%3EBene%3C%2Fem%3E%20might%20also%20be%20read%20here%20as%20the%20proper%20name%20Binnui%3B%20%3Cem%3EYehudah%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20probably%20another%20name%20for%20Hodaviah.%20Compare%202%3A40%3B%20Neh%207%3A43%3B%201%26%23xA0%3BEsdras%205%3A58.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20They%20were%20helped%20in%20this%20task%20by%20the%20Levites%20of%20the%20family%20of%20Henadad.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_10%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20builders%20completed%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%2C%20the%20priests%20put%20on%20their%20robes%20and%20took%20their%20places%20to%20blow%20their%20trumpets.%20And%20the%20Levites%2C%20descendants%20of%20Asaph%2C%20clashed%20their%20cymbals%20to%20praise%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20just%20as%20King%20David%20had%20prescribed.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_11%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EWith%20praise%20and%20thanks%2C%20they%20sang%20this%20song%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BHe%20is%20so%20good!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3EHis%20faithful%20love%20for%20Israel%20endures%20forever!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-fl-sp%22%3EThen%20all%20the%20people%20gave%20a%20great%20shout%2C%20praising%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20because%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Temple%20had%20been%20laid.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_12%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20many%20of%20the%20older%20priests%2C%20Levites%2C%20and%20other%20leaders%20who%20had%20seen%20the%20first%20Temple%20wept%20aloud%20when%20they%20saw%20the%20new%20Temple%26%23x2019%3Bs%20foundation.%20The%20others%2C%20however%2C%20were%20shouting%20for%20joy.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_3_13%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%223%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20joyful%20shouting%20and%20weeping%20mingled%20together%20in%20a%20loud%20noise%20that%20could%20be%20heard%20far%20in%20the%20distance.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_4_1%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EEzra%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EEnemies%20Oppose%20the%20Rebuilding%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20enemies%20of%20Judah%20and%20Benjamin%20heard%20that%20the%20exiles%20were%20rebuilding%20a%20Temple%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_4_2%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20they%20approached%20Zerubbabel%20and%20the%20other%20leaders%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BLet%20us%20build%20with%20you%2C%20for%20we%20worship%20your%20God%20just%20as%20you%20do.%20We%20have%20sacrificed%20to%20him%20ever%20since%20King%20Esarhaddon%20of%20Assyria%20brought%20us%20here.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_4_3%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Zerubbabel%2C%20Jeshua%2C%20and%20the%20other%20leaders%20of%20Israel%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20may%20have%20no%20part%20in%20this%20work.%20We%20alone%20will%20build%20the%20Temple%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20just%20as%20King%20Cyrus%20of%20Persia%20commanded%20us.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_4_4%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20the%20local%20residents%20tried%20to%20discourage%20and%20frighten%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20to%20keep%20them%20from%20their%20work.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22ezra_4_5%22%20bk%3D%22ezra%22%20ch%3D%224%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20bribed%20agents%20to%20work%20a